value.def: A deck on a vehicle such as a bus or ship is a lower or upper area of it.

example.ex: ...sitting on the top deck of the number 13 bus.
example.tran: 坐在 13 路公共汽车的顶层

example.ex: ...a luxury liner with five passenger decks.
example.tran: 有上下5层乘客舱的豪华游轮

value.def: The deck of a ship is the top part of it that forms a floor in the open air which you can walk on.

example.ex: She stood on the deck and waved.
example.tran: 她站在甲板上挥手告别。

value.def: A tape deck or record deck is a piece of equipment on which you play tapes or records.

example.ex: I stuck a tape in the deck.
example.tran: 我把一盘磁带放进带仓里。

value.tran: (录音机的)走带装置，匣仓;(唱机的)转盘支托面

value.def: A deck of cards is a complete set of playing cards.

example.ex: Matt picked up the cards and shuffled the deck.

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, usually use 英国英语通常用 pack

value.def: A deck is a flat wooden area next to a house, where people can sit and relax or eat.

example.ex: A natural timber deck leads into the main room of the home.
example.tran: 有一个天然的木制平台通到房子的客厅。

value.def: If something is decked with pretty things, it is decorated with them.

example.ex: Villagers decked the streets with bunting...
The house was decked with flowers.

value.def: If someone decks you, they hit you so that you fall over.

example.ex: I hear you decked him and scared the hell out of his buddies.
example.tran: 我听说你一拳把他打倒在地，吓得他那些狐朋狗友屁滚尿流。

value.def: If someone or something is below decks, they are inside a ship in the part of it that is underneath the deck.

example.ex: The crew of the trawler were gathered below decks.
example.tran: 托网渔船上的船员被聚集到甲板下。

value.def: If you clear the decks, you get ready to start something new by finishing any work that has to be done or getting rid of any problems that are in the way.

example.ex: The hostage release could clear the decks for war.
example.tran: 人质的获释可能会为发动战争扫清障碍。

example.ex: Clear the decks before you think of taking on any more responsibilities.
example.tran: 在考虑承担更多责任之前一定要先料理完手头的事。

value.tran: 清除障碍以准备开始新的工作（或行动）

value.def: If someone or something hits the deck, they fall to the ground.
